Direct Known Subclasses:
ConstrainedQuery
public class WritableTableQuery extends TableQuery<IWritableRow>
WritableTableQuery provides a base for writing to the database from a TableQuery. This includes validating rows, by passing IRowPredicate objects to addValidator(IRowPredicate), to evaluate against rows before they're submitted to the database.

  • Method Details

    • constructDRowsList

      protected Dependable<javafx.collections.ObservableList<IWritableRow>> constructDRowsList()
      This method at WritableTableQuery overrides BaseQuery.constructDRowsList() to add support for writable rows.

      constructDRowsList is called once during the initialization of a BaseQuery to provide the value of BaseQuery.rowsList. constructDRowsList uses BaseQuery<R extends IBaseRow<?>>.BQRowsList as a default implementation in BaseQuery.
      Overriding this method and subclassing BaseQuery.BQRowsList may be an integral part of configuring the rowsList you want to use in a subclass of BaseQuery.
      Overrides:
      constructDRowsList in class BaseQuery<IWritableRow>
      Returns:
      A Dependable which is stored in BaseQuery.rowsList
